The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Tharanga slams maiden century

Bogra: Upul Tharanga slammed an impressive maiden century to help Sri Lanka take a handy first innings lead over Bangladesh in the second and final Test here on Thursday. 

The elegant left-hander struck a timely unbeaten 160 as Sri Lanka, struggling on 43 for four at one stage, stretched to 302 for eight on Day II in reply to the home sides 234. 

The 21-year-old opener smashed 19 fours and two sixes. Lasith Malinga was keeping him company on a determined 12 off 64 deliveries at the close. 

 (AFP) 




